# Cloudflare Authenticated Origin Pull CA
#
# Source: https://developers.cloudflare.com/ssl/static/authenticated_origin_pull_ca.pem
#
# This file is the canonical Cloudflare-published CA whose certificates
# are presented by Cloudflare edge nodes when connecting to your origin
# with Authenticated Origin Pulls (AOP) enabled. edge-ingress is
# configured to require client certificates signed by this CA on every
# TLS handshake.
#
# At deploy time, this PEM file is materialised into a Kubernetes
# ConfigMap (`cloudflare-aop-ca`) and mounted into the edge-ingress pod
# at `/etc/edge-ingress/cloudflare/origin-pull-ca.pem`. The Rust TLS
# layer reads the path from the `tls.client_auth.ca_path` field in
# `edge-ingress.yaml`.
#
# IMPORTANT: This file is intentionally a placeholder in the git tree.
# Operators MUST replace it with the actual PEM bytes fetched from the
# canonical URL above before deploying to staging or production. The
# refresh-cloudflare-ips.sh script validates the SHA-256 fingerprint
# against the value pinned in the script header to detect tampering.
#
# To populate this file from a developer workstation:
#
#   curl -fsSL \
#     https://developers.cloudflare.com/ssl/static/authenticated_origin_pull_ca.pem \
#     -o deployments/cloudflare/origin-pull/origin-pull-ca.pem
#
# To validate the fingerprint:
#
#   openssl x509 -in deployments/cloudflare/origin-pull/origin-pull-ca.pem \
#     -noout -fingerprint -sha256
#
# In production, the actual PEM is delivered via the
# `cloudflare-aop-ca` ExternalSecret resolved from Vault at
# `etradie/services/edge-ingress/cloudflare/aop_ca`, NOT from this
# committed file. The committed file is used only by the local docker
# compose `edge` profile so developers can exercise the full
# Cloudflare -> edge-ingress -> envoy -> gateway path against a local
# self-issued AOP CA.
#
# -----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
# (Cloudflare-published bytes inserted here by operator at deploy time)
# -----END CERTIFICATE-----
